---
// src/pages/science/influenza-history.astro
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import InfluenzaTimeline from "../../components/science/InfluenzaTimeline";
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Influenza Strain History (1976â€“2026)"
  description="50 years of influenza strains and vaccine compositions. Interactive timeline showing H1N1, H3N2 dominance and pandemic years."
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-900 to-slate-800 text-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <nav class="text-sm text-slate-400 mb-4">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <a href="/science/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Science</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-white">Influenza History</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Influenza Strain History</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 max-w-3xl">
        50 years of circulating influenza strains and vaccine compositions (1976â€“2026).
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key Events -->
  <section class="py-8 bg-amber-50 border-b border-amber-200">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-amber-800 mb-4">Key Events Relevant to The Axonal Highway Hypothesis</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-amber-200">
          <div class="text-amber-600 font-mono font-bold">1977â€“1978</div>
          <div class="font-bold text-slate-800">Russian Flu (H1N1)</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Re-emergence of H1N1 after 20-year absence. Lab escape theory.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-4 border-2 border-red-400">
          <div class="text-red-600 font-mono font-bold">2009â€“2010</div>
          <div class="font-bold text-red-800">Swine Flu Pandemic (H1N1pdm09)</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-red-700">ðŸ”´ <strong>Pandemrix vaccination â†’ Narcolepsy epidemic</strong></p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-4 border border-blue-200">
          <div class="text-blue-600 font-mono font-bold">2016â€“2017</div>
          <div class="font-bold text-slate-800">H3N2 Dominant Season</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">ðŸŸ¡ Coincides with Havana Syndrome onset (speculative)</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Interactive Timeline -->
  <section class="py-8">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <InfluenzaTimeline client:load />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Context -->
  <section class="py-12 bg-slate-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Relevance to the Hypothesis</h2>
      
      <div class="prose-science">
        <h3>H1N1 and Sleep Disorders</h3>
        <p>
          The hypothesis proposes that H1N1 influenza has specific affinity for <strong>GT1b ganglioside</strong>, 
          which may be enriched in orexin-producing neurons. Historical evidence supports a connection 
          between H1N1 and sleep disorders:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>1918:</strong> Spanish Flu (H1N1) â†’ Encephalitis lethargica epidemic</li>
          <li><strong>2009:</strong> Swine Flu (H1N1pdm09) â†’ Pandemrix â†’ Narcolepsy</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>H3N2 and Auditory Symptoms</h3>
        <p>
          The speculative <a href="/speculation/havana-syndrome/">Havana Syndrome hypothesis</a> proposes that 
          H3N2 influenza may have affinity for <strong>GM3 ganglioside</strong>, which is essential for 
          cochlear function. The 2016â€“2017 season saw dominant H3N2 circulation coinciding with the 
          onset of Havana Syndrome cases.
        </p>

        <h3>Ganglioside-Specific Neurotropism</h3>
        <p>
          Different influenza subtypes may target different neuronal populations based on their 
          ganglioside binding preferences:
        </p>
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b bg-slate-200">
              <th class="text-left py-2 px-3">Subtype</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 px-3">Ganglioside</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 px-3">Target Cells</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 px-3">Potential Syndrome</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b">
              <td class="py-2 px-3 font-mono">H1N1</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3">GT1b</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3">Orexin neurons</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3">Narcolepsy</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b">
              <td class="py-2 px-3 font-mono">H3N2</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3">GM3</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3">Spiral ganglion</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3">Auditory symptoms</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- References -->
  <section class="py-8 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">References</h2>
      <ol class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-2 list-decimal list-inside">
        <li>
          WHO Global Influenza Programme (2024). Recommended composition of influenza virus vaccines. 
          <a href="https://www.who.int/publications/i/item/recommended-composition-of-influenza-virus-vaccines-for-use-in-the-2024-2025-northern-hemisphere-influenza-season" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline" target="_blank">WHO</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          WHO Global Influenza Programme (2025). Recommended composition for 2025-2026. 
          <a href="https://www.who.int/publications/i/item/recommended-composition-of-influenza-virus-vaccines-for-use-in-the-2025-2026-northern-hemisphere-influenza-season" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline" target="_blank">WHO</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          CDC (2024). Influenza (Flu) - Past Seasons Summary. 
          <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/flu/about/season/past-seasons.html" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline" target="_blank">CDC</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          Harper SA, et al. (2005). Prevention and control of influenza: recommendations of ACIP. 
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.15585/mmwr.rr5408a1" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline" target="_blank">MMWR</a>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
